article.headline: Louisville 77, Houston 75 (OT)
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Jazz Covington scored a season-high 30 points to
help Louisville beat No. 25 Houston 77-75 in overtime Sunday,
snapping the Cougars' 10-game winning streak.

Sara Nord made two free throws with 34 seconds left to give the
Lady Cards (11-8, 3-3 Conference USA) the lead, and Covington made
one free throw with 27 seconds to go for the final margin.

Nicole Oliver's desperation 3-pointer hit the front of the iron
with seven seconds remaining, and Covington got her ninth rebound
of the game to secure the win.

Houston (15-3, 4-1) rallied from a six-point deficit in the
second half to tie the game on a 3-pointer by Chandi Jones with 31
seconds to go in regulation.

Houston led 26-22 at halftime. The game had 17 lead changes and
nine ties.

Sancho Lyttle had 25 points, 15 rebounds and six steals to lead
Houston.

Nord added 16 points, including 8-of-8 from the free-throw line,
and 13 assists.
